--- a/docs/architecture.md
+++ b/docs/architecture.md
@@ -95,8 +95,12 @@ port when the requested address is unavailable.
 
 - `AgentBackend::launch` starts an agent session from an `AgentLaunch`.
 - `AgentBackend::send` sends a prompt to an existing agent session.
+- `AgentBackend::command` executes a provider command against an existing agent session. The default
+  implementation returns an unsupported-command chat message, so external providers can opt in to
+  command handling without changing their basic launch/send implementation.
 - `AgentBackend::launch_streaming` and `AgentBackend::send_streaming` provide real-time output to a
-  sink of `AgentStreamEvent` values. Their default implementations call the non-streaming methods.
+  sink of `AgentStreamEvent` values. `AgentBackend::command_streaming` is the matching streaming
+  command hook. Their default implementations call the non-streaming methods.
 - `AgentBackend::shutdown_handle` returns an `AgentShutdownHandle` for terminating active provider
   processes.
 - `AgentStreamEvent` carries status text, streamed agent messages, and streamed errors.
@@ -127,6 +131,10 @@ public lifecycle extension is required before external child processes can parti
   `codex exec` and `codex exec resume` calls. Launch invocations include the injected
   `PromptPolicy`; resumed invocations for known sessions pass only the follow-up message because the
   Codex thread already contains the launch-time policy and repository instructions.
+- `CodexBackend` handles backend commands without sending slash-command text through the normal
+  resume prompt path. `/status` renders the selected session's known Codex thread id, feature,
+  activity state, and message count from backend state. `/fork` reports the selected source thread
+  and optional fork prompt as backend command output.
 - `CodexBackend::record_launch_reply`, `record_launch_output`, and `session` maintain in-memory
   session state.
 - `CodexBackend` parses Codex `--json` event lines from stdout to capture `thread.started`
@@ -167,6 +175,12 @@ The primary public methods are:
 `CommandChat` uses the active `AgentProfile` when launching user agents, reviewers, and linearizers.
 Workflow code must not hard-code `AgentKind::Codex` when the active profile supplies the provider.
 
+Selected-agent chat text that starts with `/` followed by a non-whitespace command token is a backend
+command for that selected agent. `CommandChat::send_to_agent_streaming_with_ids` routes that input to
+`AgentBackend::command_streaming` and returns the backend command output as the agent chat reply; it
+does not send the slash command through the normal prompt/resume path and does not process the output
+as orchestrator directives.
+
 ## UI-Neutral Controller
 
 `src/workspace.rs::WorkLeafController<B>` is the preferred API for frontends. It owns UI-neutral
